File: A man walks past the words "Coronavirus" painted on a wall, amid the spread of the coronavirus disease (COVID-19) outbreak, in Soweto, South Africa, May 31, 2020. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has reported 572 new COVID-19 related deaths in the last 24 hours. 400 of those deaths were reported in the Eastern Cape. 114 further deaths were reported in Gauteng, 35 in the Western Cape, 18 in KZN and 5 in the Free State. READ: SA reports less COVID-19 cases for 2nd consecutive day The number of confirmed cases jumped by more than 13,000. There's now 394, 948 confirmed COVID-19 cases. The country's recovery rate has improved even further to 58 percent. This means almost 230,000 people have already recovered. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.